{"title":"•Piperacilina-tazobactam(Zosyn,Tazocin)-2024","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/General/•Piperacilina-tazobactam(Zosyn,Tazocin)-2024.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"• Piperacilina-tazobactam\\N(Zosyn, Tazocin)","guid":"E-lZNL5otiz5ymQM2nCekQ","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Uso y Dosificación","guid":"","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"• Descripción: Piperacilina-tazobactam es una combinación del antibiótico antipseudomónico\\NPiperacilina con el inhibidor de β-lactamasa Tazobactam.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"3","parent":"1","text":"• Protección: Tazobactam protege Piperacilina de la degradación por\\Nlas β-lactamasas de MSSA, H. influenzae, M. catarrhalis y B. fragilis.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"1","text":"• No aumenta actividad: Tazobactam no aumenta\\Nla actividad de Piperacilina contra P. aeruginosa.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"1","text":"• Formas de dosificación IV:\\NSiempre en proporción 8:1.","guid":"","children":[{"id":"6","parent":"5","text":"• 2.25 gm vial (Piperacilina 2 gm + Tazobactam 0.25 gm)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"7","parent":"5","text":"• 3.375 gm vial (Piperacilina 3 gm + Tazobactam 0.375 gm)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"8","parent":"5","text":"• 4.5 gm vial (Piperacilina 4 gm + Tazobactam 0.5 gm)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"9","parent":"1","text":"• Evitar uso: No se recomienda Piperacilina-Tazobactam para\\Ninfecciones por bacilos gram-negativos aeróbicos productores de BLEE+.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"10","parent":"1","text":"Dosis en Adultos","guid":"","children":[{"id":"11","parent":"10","text":"• Regímenes estándar:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"12","parent":"11","text":"• Peritonitis, absceso intraabdominal: 3.375 gm IV q6h o 4.5 gm IV q8h (infección grave)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"13","parent":"11","text":"• Neumonía por P. aeruginosa: 3.375 gm IV q4h o 4.5 gm IV q6h","guid":"","children":[{"id":"14","parent":"13","text":"• Combinar con: Aminoglucósido antipseudomónico o fluoroquinolona","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"15","parent":"10","text":"• Regímenes de\\Ninfusión prolongada:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"16","parent":"15","text":"• 4.5 gm IV en 30 min, seguido 4 horas después por 3.375 gm IV\\N(infundido en 4 horas) q8h.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"17","parent":"1","text":"Dosis en Pediatría","guid":"","children":[{"id":"18","parent":"17","text":"• Dosis (Edad >28 días):","guid":"","children":[{"id":"19","parent":"18","text":"• 300-400 mg/kg/día (dividido q6h)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"20","parent":"17","text":"• Recomendaciones del fabricante\\N(diciembre 2022, ≤40 kg):","guid":"","children":[{"id":"21","parent":"20","text":"• Apendicitis/peritonitis, 2-9 meses: 80 mg/kg q8h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"22","parent":"20","text":"• Apendicitis/peritonitis, >9 meses: 100 mg/kg q8h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"23","parent":"20","text":"• Neumonía nosocomial, 2-9 meses: 80 mg/kg q6h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"24","parent":"20","text":"• Neumonía nosocomial, >9 meses: 100 mg/kg q6h","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"25","parent":"1","text":"Ajuste Renal","guid":"","children":[{"id":"26","parent":"25","text":"• Peso corporal y depuración\\Nde creatinina (CrCl):","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"27","parent":"25","text":"• Función renal normal:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"28","parent":"27","text":"• Vida media: Pip 1 hr, Tazo 1 hr","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"29","parent":"25","text":"• ESRD:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"30","parent":"29","text":"• Vida media: Pip 3-5 hr, Tazo 2.8 hr","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"31","parent":"25","text":"• Dosis (función renal normal): 3. 375 gm (en 30 min) q6h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"32","parent":"25","text":"• CrCl >40: 3.375 gm q6h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"33","parent":"25","text":"• CrCl 20-40: 2. 25 gm q6h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"34","parent":"25","text":"• CrCl <20: 2.25 gm q8h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"35","parent":"25","text":"• HD: 2.25 gm q12h (+ dosis extra 0.75 gm AD)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"36","parent":"25","text":"• CAPD: 2.25 gm q12h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"37","parent":"25","text":"• CRRT: 2.25 gm q6h","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"38","parent":"1","text":"Ajuste Hepático: Ninguno","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"39","parent":"1","text":"Otros Ajustes","guid":"","children":[{"id":"40","parent":"39","text":"• Obesidad: Ver tabla de ajustes de dosis en obesidad.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"41","parent":"39","text":"• ECMO: Ver tabla de ajustes de dosis en ECMO.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"42","parent":"1","text":"Efectos Adversos","guid":"","children":[{"id":"43","parent":"42","text":"• Disfunción plaquetaria: Puede ocurrir en pacientes con insuficiencia renal, debido a la agregación plaquetaria deteriorada.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"44","parent":"42","text":"• Trombocitopenia inmune inducida por fármacos: También puede ocurrir\\Ncon Vancomicina y pacientes a menudo expuestos a la combinación.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"45","parent":"42","text":"• Reacciones alérgicas: Posibles con cualquier antibiótico β-lactámico.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"46","parent":"42","text":"• Tratamiento detenido: Debido a efectos adversos (3.2%): flebitis local (1%), fiebre (2%), rash (4%), enfermedad del\\Nsuero, Coombs positivo, neutropenia, eosinofilia, trombocitopenia, ↑ PT/PTT, náuseas/vómitos (7%), diarrea (11%),\\Ncolitis por C. difficile, ↑ LFTs, ↑ BUN/Creatinina, cefalea (8%), confusión (raro), convulsiones (raro).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"47","parent":"42","text":"• Hipokalemia: Posible aumento de la incidencia de lesión renal aguda al combinar con Vancomicina.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"48","parent":"1","text":"Riesgo en Embarazo","guid":"","children":[{"id":"49","parent":"48","text":"• Categoría de riesgo FDA 1: Datos humanos insuficientes, evidencia de fetotoxicidad en animales.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"50","parent":"48","text":"• Uso durante lactancia: Concentraciones bajas en leche, no se esperan efectos adversos.\\NMonitorear toxicidad GI en el infante.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"51","parent":"0","text":"Espectro\\NAntimicrobiano","guid":"","children":[{"id":"52","parent":"51","text":"RECOMENDADO ++ (8)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"53","parent":"52","text":"• B. fragilis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"54","parent":"52","text":"• C. koseri","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"55","parent":"52","text":"• Capnocytophaga sp.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"56","parent":"52","text":"• E. coli (S)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"57","parent":"52","text":"• Klebsiella oxytoca (S)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"58","parent":"52","text":"• Klebsiella pneumoniae (S)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"59","parent":"52","text":"• M. morganii","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"60","parent":"52","text":"• P. aeruginosa","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"61","parent":"51","text":"ACTIVO + (35)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"62","parent":"61","text":"• Actinomyces sp.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"63","parent":"61","text":"• Aeromonas sp.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"64","parent":"61","text":"• Arcanobacter sp.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"65","parent":"61","text":"• C. diphtheriae","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"66","parent":"61","text":"• Clostridium sp.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"67","parent":"61","text":"• E. faecalis (VS)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"68","parent":"61","text":"• Eikenella sp.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"69","parent":"61","text":"• F. necrophorum","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"70","parent":"61","text":"• H. influenzae","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"71","parent":"61","text":"• Kingella sp.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"72","parent":"61","text":"• L. monocytogenes","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"73","